<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Privacy Policy - BlueBaħar</title>

  <meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow" />

  <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/apple-touch-icon.png">
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="/favicon-32x32.png">
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="16x16" href="/favicon-16x16.png">
  <link rel="manifest" href="/site.webmanifest">

  <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>

  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fredoka:wght@500;600;700&family=Montserrat:wght@300;400;500;600;700;800&family=Roboto:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />

  <script>
    tailwind.config = {
      theme: {
        extend: {
          colors: {
            sky: '#78C3EA',
            ink: '#152051',
            paper: '#FEFEFE',
            good: '#5C946E',
            warning: '#FFC857',
            bad: '#D80C2B',
          },
          fontFamily: {
            display: ['Montserrat', 'sans-serif'],
            body: ['Roboto', 'sans-serif'],
            brand: ['Fredoka', 'sans-serif'],
          },
          boxShadow: {
            soft: '0 24px 80px -36px rgba(21, 32, 81, 0.55)',
            glow: '0 18px 50px -28px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95)',
          },
        },
      },
    };
  </script>

  <style>
    :root {
      --ink: #152051;
      --sky: #78C3EA;
      --paper: #FEFEFE;
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; }

    html { min-height: 100%; scroll-behavior: smooth; }

    body {
      min-height: 100vh;
      min-height: 100svh;
      color: var(--ink);
      background-color: var(--sky);
      background-image:
        radial-gradient(circle at 22% 14%, rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.45) 0, rgba(254, 254, 254, 0) 28%),
        radial-gradient(circle at 82% 76%, rgba(21, 32, 81, 0.10) 0, rgba(21, 32, 81, 0) 30%),
        radial-gradient(circle, rgba(21, 32, 81, 0.055) 0.5px, transparent 0.6px);
      background-size: auto, auto, 6px 6px;
      font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
      text-rendering: geometricPrecision;
      -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
    }

    .doc {
      background-color: rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.92);
      backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
      box-shadow: 0 24px 80px -36px rgba(21, 32, 81, 0.55);
    }

    .doc h2 {
      font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }

    .doc p, .doc li { line-height: 1.7; }

    .doc a {
      color: #152051;
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
      text-decoration-thickness: 1.5px;
    }

    .doc a:hover { text-decoration-thickness: 2.5px; }

    .accent-line {
      width: clamp(48px, 10vw, 100px);
      height: 3px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, #152051 0%, rgba(21, 32, 81, 0.28) 100%);
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="mx-auto flex min-h-screen min-h-[100svh] w-full max-w-3xl flex-col px-5 py-8 sm:px-8 sm:py-12">
    <header class="flex items-center gap-4">
      <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-3 transition hover:opacity-90" aria-label="BlueBaħar home">
        <img
          src="/logo.png"
          alt="BlueBaħar"
          class="h-12 w-12 shrink-0 select-none rounded-2xl bg-paper/30 p-1 shadow-glow ring-1 ring-paper/40 sm:h-14 sm:w-14"
          draggable="false"
        />
        <span class="select-none font-brand text-xl font-semibold text-paper drop-shadow-sm sm:text-2xl">
          BlueBaħar <small>{{version}}</small>
        </span>
      </a>
    </header>

    <main class="doc mt-8 flex-1 rounded-2xl px-6 py-8 sm:mt-12 sm:rounded-3xl sm:px-12 sm:py-12">
      <p class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-ink/55">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink sm:text-4xl">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <div class="accent-line mt-5"></div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-ink/60">Last updated: 4 June 2026</p>

      <section class="mt-8 space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl text-ink sm:text-2xl">In short</h2>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          BlueBaħar does not require an account and does not collect information that identifies
          you personally. The app is a read-only viewer for public maritime data published by the
          Maltese authorities. Your device location and notifications stay on your device. To keep
          the app reliable we collect anonymous usage statistics and crash reports through
          privacy-focused third-party services, and we rely on Apple, Google, and RevenueCat to
          manage subscriptions — none of which receives information that identifies you.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8 space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl text-ink sm:text-2xl">1. What we don't collect</h2>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          We do not operate user accounts and we do not serve advertising or use advertising SDKs.
          We do not collect your name, email address, contacts, photos, precise persistent
          identifiers, or any other information that identifies you personally.
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          We do collect a limited amount of anonymous, non-identifying information to operate and
          improve the app — namely anonymous usage statistics and crash reports. The sections below
          explain exactly what this involves and which providers are used.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8 space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl text-ink sm:text-2xl">2. Geolocation</h2>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          If you grant the app location permission, BlueBaħar uses your device's geolocation
          services to display your current position on the map together with notices to mariners,
          hazards, restricted zones, protected areas, and weather forecasts.
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          Location data is processed locally on your device. It is not transmitted to our
          servers, stored remotely, or shared with any third party. You can revoke the
          permission at any time from your device settings; the rest of the app will continue
          to work without it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8 space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl text-ink sm:text-2xl">3. Notifications</h2>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          BlueBaħar can show local notifications on your device — for example, reminders or alerts
          generated by the app itself. These notifications are scheduled and delivered entirely on
          your device. We do not operate push notifications from our servers, and the notification
          permission does not transmit any data off your device. You can grant or revoke the
          permission at any time from your device settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8 space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl text-ink sm:text-2xl">4. Anonymous usage analytics</h2>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          To understand how the app is used and to improve it, we collect anonymous usage data
          using <a href="https://posthog.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PostHog</a>.
          This includes information such as which screens are viewed, which features are used, and
          basic technical details (app version, device model, operating system, and approximate
          region). PostHog assigns each install a randomly generated, anonymous identifier so usage
          can be counted without identifying you.
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          This data is not linked to your name, email, or any personal information — because we do
          not ask for any — and is used only in aggregate to measure and improve the app. We do not
          use it for advertising. PostHog's handling of this information is governed by its own
          privacy policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8 space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl text-ink sm:text-2xl">5. Crash and error reporting</h2>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          When the app encounters an error or crash, we collect a diagnostic report using
          <a href="https://sentry.io/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sentry</a> so we can
          find and fix the problem. A report typically contains technical information such as the
          error and stack trace, the app version, the device model, and the operating system
          version, along with an anonymous identifier.
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          We do not attach your name, email, or other personal information to these reports. The
          data is used solely for diagnosing and fixing problems with the app. Sentry's handling of
          this information is governed by its own privacy policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8 space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl text-ink sm:text-2xl">6. App updates</h2>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          BlueBaħar uses <a href="https://expo.dev/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Expo</a>
          to deliver over-the-air updates to the app. When the app checks for an update, your device
          contacts Expo's servers and sends standard technical information (such as the app and
          runtime version and the platform) so the correct update can be returned. This is not used
          to identify you. Expo's handling of that information is governed by its own privacy policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8 space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl text-ink sm:text-2xl">7. Data shown in the app</h2>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          The information shown in BlueBaħar is fetched from our backend, which in turn
          retrieves and aggregates publicly available open data published by the Government of
          Malta and its agencies (notices to mariners, marine protected areas, weather
          forecasts and similar published datasets).
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          When the app fetches this data, your device makes ordinary HTTPS requests to our
          backend. Like any web service, our infrastructure may briefly process technical
          information (such as IP address) for the sole purpose of delivering the response and
          protecting the service from abuse. This information is not used to identify you and
          is not retained beyond what is necessary for those operational purposes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8 space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl text-ink sm:text-2xl">8. Map tiles</h2>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          The map background is rendered using third-party map tile providers. When tiles are
          loaded, your device communicates directly with the tile provider, which may receive
          standard request information (such as IP address and the map area being viewed)
          subject to that provider's own privacy policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8 space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl text-ink sm:text-2xl">9. Subscriptions</h2>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          BlueBaħar is free to use for the first month after install. After that, continued
          access requires a monthly subscription, purchased through the Apple App Store or
          Google Play. Payment, billing, refunds, and renewals are handled entirely by Apple
          or Google under your existing store account — we never see or process your payment
          details.
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          We use <a href="https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RevenueCat</a>
          as our subscription management provider. RevenueCat assigns each install an
          anonymous identifier and records your subscription status (active, in trial, or
          expired) so the app knows whether to grant access. This identifier is not linked
          to your name, email, or any personal information — because we do not ask for any.
          RevenueCat may also receive standard technical information from your device (such
          as platform, app version, and country) for the sole purpose of validating your
          subscription. Its handling of that information is governed by RevenueCat's own
          privacy policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8 space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl text-ink sm:text-2xl">10. Children</h2>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          BlueBaħar is not directed at children. Because we do not collect personal
          information from anyone, we likewise do not knowingly collect any from children.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8 space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl text-ink sm:text-2xl">11. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          We may update this policy from time to time. The latest version is always available
          at this page, with the "last updated" date at the top.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8 space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl text-ink sm:text-2xl">12. Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-ink/80">
          For any privacy-related question, write to info_AT_bluebahar_DOT_com.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="mt-8 flex flex-col items-center gap-2 text-sm text-paper/85 sm:flex-row sm:justify-between">
      <a href="/" class="font-display font-medium underline-offset-4 hover:underline">← Back to BlueBaħar</a>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
        <a href="/tos" class="font-display font-medium underline-offset-4 hover:underline">Terms of Service</a>
        <span class="text-paper/65">© 2026 Impossible Labs</span>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
